<collectingCountry box="[264,409,404,430]" name="Ecuador" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">ECUADOR</collectingCountry>
, Napo, Coca, Napo R., 
<date box="[686,767,404,430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1965-05">
v. 
<number box="[705,767,404,430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</date>
, L. Pena, 
<quantity box="[883,957,404,430]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" unit="m" value="250.0">250 m</quantity>
(
<number box="[973,989,404,430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
Ψ 
<collectionCode box="[1015,1080,404,430]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/y2kv-9w3k" name="Canadian National Collection of Insects, Arachnids, and Nematodes" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">CNC</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1325,283,790]" box="[312,834,444,470]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
<typeStatus box="[312,421,444,470]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Holotype</typeStatus>
condition. Terminalia in glycerine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1325,283,790]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
Etymology. The specific name is in honor of Mr Luis E. Peña who made significant contributions to entomology and collected the 
<typeStatus box="[809,860,524,550]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1325,283,790]" box="[312,925,564,590]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Variation. Ecuadorian specimens have darker coxae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1325,283,790]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
Discussion. 
<taxonomicName box="[409,515,604,630]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penai">
<emphasis box="[409,433,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[450,515,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">penai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is apparently most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart" authorityName="Macquart" box="[875,1196,604,630]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis box="[875,1053,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
(Macquart)
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[331,406,644,670]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in that both have a rather short tergite 
<number box="[889,905,644,670]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
, which is blunted in 
<taxonomicName box="[1163,1270,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penai">
<emphasis box="[1163,1270,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. penai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and bears two distal clefts in 
<taxonomicName box="[564,742,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis box="[564,742,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They differ in the shape of the male terminalia, mainly in the hypandrium, which is slender and without setae in 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1137,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penai">
<emphasis box="[1032,1137,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. penai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and broad with distinct posterior setae in 
<taxonomicName box="[565,740,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis box="[565,740,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
